# Copy to `.env` and fill in values. Never commit `.env`.

# --- Spotify (https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard)
# Web Playback SDK requires a Spotify Premium account for the connecting user.
# If we add OAuth scopes, use “Re-authorize” in the Mixer so Spotify grants the new scopes.
#
# Dev server binds to http://127.0.0.1:3000 (see package.json `dev` script).
# Redirect URI in Spotify Dashboard (exact match, one line is enough for local dev):
#   http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/auth/callback/spotify
# Localhost and IPv6 loopback are normalized to 127.0.0.1 for OAuth. Production:
#   https://<your-production-domain>/api/auth/callback/spotify
# Tunnels: the app uses X-Forwarded-Host / X-Forwarded-Proto when set; add that HTTPS
# callback URL to Spotify, or set SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI to the public callback URL.
#
# Optional: force a single redirect URL (e.g. reverse proxy / tunnel):
# SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI=https://example.com/api/auth/callback/spotify
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=

# --- Database (Prisma)
# Local SQLite file (path relative to project root).
DATABASE_URL="file:./prisma/dev.db"

# --- PWA
# Service worker registers in production builds only. Test install: `npm run build && npm start`
# over HTTPS (or localhost). Spotify playback on mobile still requires a user tap to start audio.

# --- Vercel / production notes
# - Add the same variables in: Project Settings → Environment Variables.
# - SQLite on `file:` does not persist on Vercel serverless (ephemeral filesystem).
#   For production, point DATABASE_URL at Turso/libsql or another hosted DB and use
#   Prisma’s libsql adapter or migrate the data layer in a later phase.
